Description:
The Supplier Change Request (SCR) process is to ensure ALL changes to the purchase part use are managed and comply to ASM’s requirement to build identical tools to our customers. This is needed to ensure compliance to ASM Copy Exactly Program. All products (to be) used in and/or for ASM equipment will have to remain identical unless changes have been approved by ASM through the SCR process. Therefore it is ASM policy to control all changes in design, technical product documentation and/or supply chain that can affect ASM equipment regarding:
· Safety/ergonomics;
· Performance;
· Reliability;
· Functionality;
· Quality;
· Cleanliness;
· Serviceability/maintainability;
· Configuration;
· Footprint;
· Software;
· Installation and facilities hook-up;
· Appearance; and
· Ability to interchange, substitute or replace spare parts, sub-assemblies and or software (including embedded controllers).
Changes can also occur by modifying:
· Raw materials or other resources used directly or indirectly in the equipment;
· Equipment and sub assembly manufacturing location, conditions or environment;
· Sequence of events (manufacturing, fabrication, assembly, test, packaging, printing); and
· Sub-suppliers.
